# Flutter UI Rules

- Keep UI code inside `app/lib/src/` using feature-first folders.
- Route all core lifecycle and stats operations through a dedicated FFI service layer.
- Keep UI interactions async; avoid blocking work on the main isolate.
- Read display text through i18n keys, not hard-coded user-facing strings.
- Keep platform-specific behavior behind adapters to preserve cross-platform parity.

## Example

```dart
// BAD: await heavy call directly in build()
// GOOD: trigger async load from controller/service and render from state
```
